summary: Surrey is a county in southeast England, bordering London and other nearby counties. It covers an area of 1,663 kmÂ² and has a population of over 1.2 million. The county is divided into eleven districts and includes towns like Woking, Guildford, and Leatherhead. The north of Surrey is more urban, while the south is rural with the North Downs, a chalky mountain range, running through it. The county is known for its forests, with the highest woodland cover in England.
title: Surrey
